content:
To answer and make calls:

You must have Contact Center Agent permission set.

Add the Phone component to the Voice Call page layout. This feature is available with Service Cloud Voice with Amazon Connect or partner telephony from Amazon Connect.

Set your availability in the Omni-Channel utility so you can make and receive calls.

Click the checkmark button to answer a call. A timer will display showing the duration since you accepted the call.

To dial an outbound call, enter the phone number and click Call.

Put the caller on hold by clicking Pause, and resume the call by clicking Play.

End the call by clicking the X button or End Call.

Silence your line by clicking Mute, and pause a call recording by clicking Recording.
title: Service Cloud Voice Call Features
